author: seattlepi.com
title: Evergreen High football player dies from injuries
text:
A senior football player from Evergreen High School who was injured during a game Friday night has died.
Wide receiver and defensive back Kenney Bui was taken to Harborview Friday night, and a hospital spokesperson said Bui died Monday morning.
"This is a devastating loss for all of us -- Evergreen students, families, and staff, and our entire Highline community," said Susan Enfield, superintendent of Highline School District. "Our deepest condolences go out to Kenney's family and all who knew him. Please join us in keeping them in your thoughts and prayers."
Evergreen High School played Highline High School in a homecoming game Friday night at Highline Memorial Stadium.
District spokesperson Catherine Carbone Rogers said the injury occurred at Highline Memorial Field in the fourth quarter. It is unclear what kind of injury Bui suffered.
There are licensed and certified trainers at every game, Rogers said. "We are very, very conscious of the safety of our student athletes, and in fact, Highline goes above and beyond in safety."
Bui was one of two players seriously injured during football games in the state Friday night. A player at Adna High School broke two vertebrae, according to the state's official high school Twitter feed.
